</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="973889" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure122" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96480" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" start="Figure 122" startId="F122">
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Figure 122.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="C. E. Schnell ex Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="C. E. Schnell ex Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lancifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lancifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Conostegia lancifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="128" pageNumber="129">
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
noted that as like for 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia centronoides" order="Myrtales" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="centronoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Conostegia centronoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the holotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia centronoides subsp. var. var. lancifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="centronoides" subSpecies="var." variety="lancifolia">Conostegia centronoides var. lancifolia</taxonomicName>
was lost during the war in Berlin. I concur with 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
in that the description of the latter including stipitate stellate hairs and narrowly ovate leaves matches topotypical material which Schnell cited as the neotype (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">E. Asplund 18868</emphasis>
). For this reason and because the work of 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
wasa not published, the neotypification is made here. 
<bibRefCitation author="Schnell, CE" journalOrPublisher="Harvard University" pageId="243" pageNumber="244" refId="B77" refString="Schnell, CE, 1996. The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae). Harvard University" title="The Genus Conostegia (Melastomataceae)" year="1996">Schnell (1996)</bibRefCitation>
included in his circumscription of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="C. E. Schnell ex Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="C. E. Schnell ex Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia lancifolia" order="Myrtales" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lancifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Conostegia lancifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the decurrent leaved and large leaf blade plants here referred to as 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia ortizae" order="Myrtales" pageId="128" pageNumber="129" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ortizae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="128" pageNumber="129">Conostegia ortizae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Schnell pointed out that if intermediates between the two morphotypes did not arise they might as well be called subspecies or species. Considering they are easy to distinguish they are here proposed as different species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
